<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-bda89bcca045a7ee22a67ecd18739422c2382794">The Long Sword of the Dawn (E:25, L:2) (3d5) (+20,+20)</h2>
<em>Forged in the farthest East by a race of mighty spellcasters, this shiny pale sword gleams with the rays of rising sun as you invoke its power of commanding legions of powerful immortal warriors...</em> <p>
It is <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Spoilers_2fSentient_20Weapons"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">sentient</a>. It can be activated for summon the Legion of the Dawn every 500+d500 turns if it is being worn. It increases your charisma and infravision by 3. It does extra damage from fire. It is very sharp and can cut your foes. It is especially deadly against dragons. It strikes at demons with holy wrath. It strikes at undead with holy wrath. It fights against evil with holy fury. It sustains your  charisma. It provides immunity to paralysis. It makes you completely fearless. It provides resistance to fire, light and blindness. It speeds your regenerative powers. It can clone monsters. It provides a random high resistance or a random ability. 
</p>
